                            <comment id="14044461" author="shalinmangar" created="Thu, 26 Jun 2014 08:26:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch which re-uses an existing temp collection after deleting all documents from it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14044623" author="shalinmangar" created="Thu, 26 Jun 2014 12:49:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, the changes in this patch were not required because we were already deleting the temporary collection at the start of the migrateKey method. We only need to do the following:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;       &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;try&lt;/span&gt; {
         deleteCollection(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; ZkNodeProps(props), results);
+        clusterState = zkStateReader.getClusterState();
       } &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;catch&lt;/span&gt; (Exception e) {
         log.warn(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Unable to clean up existing temporary collection: &quot;&lt;/span&gt; + tempSourceCollectionName, e);
       }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We just need to refresh the cluster state object after deleting the collection for re-tries to work. I&apos;ll commit this change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
